Female description
: Carapace shape (
Fig. 19C
) and size similar to male. A2 (
Fig. 22C
) with long claws, G1 and G3 claws similar in size, G2 and GM setae half as long as G1, y3 seta-like. z1 and z2 setae very short, about size of terminal segment. T1 (
Fig. 22D
) with one a seta and three unequally smooth long apical setae with lengths: h2>h1>h3. b, c and d setae not apparent. Genital organ simple, rounded (
Fig. 22E
). All other parts similar to male.
